item.title: Qidi i-fast Front Gap Cover/Vent
item.description:
This was created to fill the front gap in the Qidi i-fast. It simply clips in along the inner edge of the door frame. Two sided tape can be used to secure the bottom and to secure the two pieces together. Each vent will cover half of the gap so you will need to print two.

I will eventually remix this to flare out a bit at the bottom edge to follow the contour of the printer a bit more tightly along the edges but these work well and leave very little space once installed.

I printed them using a tough PLA. Time will tell if they warp once I crank the heat up in the chamber but at 80 degrees celsius they had no issues.

item.title: Nerf 6 Dart Speed Loader
item.description:
This is a NERF/Adventure Force foam dart speed loader I designed for me and my friends. The measurements were taken off of an adventure force pro mag, but it should still fit and work fine with nerf branded mags as well (they have the same dimensions and are interchangeable) I originally designed a 12 dart speed loader to load the full mag at once, but with that length, it proved to be too much friction and you could not easily pull it out.

Check out my other Nerf/Adventure force attachments on my profile!
item.author: AlexMVW10

item.title: Texas Rummy Cube
item.description:
This is a Texas-sized version of the popular game. I made this much larger set of the original game for those who are have difficultly seeing the smaller tiles and colors. I made the tiles larger and picked high contrasting colors. I also enlarged the text relative to the tile also.

I chose to use Aces instead of jokers as a nod towards the namesake card game... which then led to a few variations: Classic 2-joker, 4-joker, color-fixed jokers, and aces high/low.

Some assembly required. Be careful not to squish the tile when pressing the text into it. You might have to file it just a pinch if your print isn't quite perfect.

The tiles are 60mm x 40mm x 6mm and the racks can hold 24 tiles.

item.title: Router Corner Template (metric)
item.description:
I've been using hanselcj's awesome router corner templates for quite some time, but since I live in a country that uses the metric system I came upon a use case where I needed a metric size. My current project is to build a router table with a custom router plate. My plan is to use the template to trimm the edges of the plate. But in order to create a perfect fit with the trimm on the table the corner radius needs to fit the size of my router bit. So far I only created a 16mm template as I only plan on using a 16mm router bit. If you need a specific size though, just let me know and I'll create it.

If my design helped you please consider buying me a coffee or at least giving me a "like". That would really mean a lot to me and validate all the time spent creating free designs.

item.title: Carbonation Cap Kegerator Font
item.description:
Here we have a new interesting remix of two projects to take this idea into a new direction for pluto tap owners.
3x PCO 1881 (aka PET Bottle tops) are attached to a standard base for fits keg-king/mangrove-jacks kegerator fridge.
Diagonal measurement from centre to centre across the circumference mounting holes is 97mm.
This is designed to suit the PET Carbonation Caps that are cheap and easily mated to this unique tap head.
the kegerator owner could reasonably buy one Pluto gun, and swap the gun between kegs.
After the session concludes, the pluto gun is then returned to the fridge or cleaned for the next session.
Simply connect each carbonation cap to beer line and whatever keg disconnect type you use on your kegs.

https://www.google.com/search?q=carbonation+caps
https://www.google.com/search?q=pluto+gun
https://www.keg-king.com.au/s4-homebrew-pack.html

this model has been printed in both PETG and ABS, and i can personally confirm PETG is preferable. Finish quality and bed adhesion was more successful with PETG.
ABS was printed at 232C and 110c bed on an ender3 pro.
PETG was printed at 232c and 100c bed on an ender3 pro.

original projects in this remix;
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3732085
thank you for the base sketch of the font >> https://www.thingiverse.com/omphteliba

https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:499261
Thank you for the PCO1881 insert used as a component (reposted here) >> https://www.thingiverse.com/jsc

Fusion 360 archive and active project for the collar
.STL's for aligning to your printer profile;

  • please print with support for the 1881 font as the PCO threads need to defy gravity.
  • print with wall thickness of 3mm
  • 15% cubic infill for the 1881 font
  • 25% lightning infill for the collar
  • layer thickness was 0.2mm on both models
  • use a brim on both models
    .gcode 'ready to go' load for instant Ender3 Print from TF.

good luck!

item.title: Adventure Time Gunter
item.description:
Hey!

This is my first upload here and perhaps (most surely) will be some errors, but please let me know in the coments (if there are any here, don't really know).
This design is free use and you can customize it at your choice , just have as much fun as I had modeling, printing and coloring. I just wanted some kind of 3d printed Gunter that was actually like Gunter, the other ones didn't really work.
So, I made it in the Artillery Genius Pro, I think that if you import it to the 3d printing software that you will use perhaps it's a little small, I just bumped it to scale 1000% and did just fine.
Then if you have some different filaments you can try to mix them, I just color it with some acrylics and warhammer paint as shown in the picture. If you have any doubt or problems relating this, (I can try to talk about your ex if you want to, but I won't be of that much use) you can DM me, no problems.

I leave bellow some specs details for supports, and the .blend if you wanna change the text in the sign or anything else. Up to you.

Have fun, Martinx. ^^

item.title: Rocinante USB Drive
item.description:
Remixed a remix of a remix to bring you a Rocinante USB thumb drive!

I used a Sandick Cruzer USB drive (https://www.amazon.ca/gp/product/B00NIEIRVY/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&psc=1) to make this.

Print on a RESIN printer, break the working bits out of the thumb drive plastic. Insert non-working end into engine part (will be a tight pressfit). Install 6x2mm magnets into holes on engine and rear body part. The magnets will stand proud on the engine part, and be recessed on the rear hull. This is BY DESIGN.

Super glue for everything, paint and done!

item.title: Wall clock
item.description:
By taking advantage of the multi-material function of Polyjet 3D printers, it is easy to consider a design in which clear resin is usually poured into a formwork and a model of a different material is confined inside.
This is a watch made by combining a model made with that function with a commercially available DIY kit.

【Nail it!!】ネイルイット ロングシャフトムーブメント ※電池別売※ / 手作り 時計 針 ストリングアート 糸かけ 曼荼羅 ハンドメイド おうち時間 DIY

*When combining with a similar kit, please make a hole after manufacturing.

  • The size of the 3D data cylinder is φ114mmx10mm.
  • There are many cavities inside the cylinder to combine the 3D of blood vessels.

Also,If you use a large 3D printer with similar functionality, you can adjust the scale and install it like a sign.
